Globe Telecom, PLDT, Universal Robina: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-05-11T00:46:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/globe-telecom-pldt-universal-robina-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close,
unless stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.1 percent to
4,303.13.  Globe Telecom Inc. (GLO)  : The  Philippines ’ second-
largest telecommunications company’s first-quarter net income
increased 1 percent to 3 billion pesos ($69.8 million), ending
four straight quarters of year-on-year declines. Mobile phone
subscribers rose 14 percent to 27.3 million from a year earlier,
it said in a statement yesterday. The stock closed unchanged at
850 pesos.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  : The
nation’s most valuable company reported net income in the first
quarter fell 6 percent to 10.73 billion pesos as revenue
declined 4 percent, it said in a statement yesterday. The stock
rose 3.1 percent to 2,480 pesos.  Universal Robina Corp. (URC)  : The food and drinks
company owned by JG Summit Holdings Corp. (JGS PM) yesterday
said net income in the first half of fiscal year 2011 fell 28
percent to 3.285 billion pesos as operating income and earnings
from investments dropped. The stock increased 0.1 percent to
38.35 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at   cyap19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
